The global tool steel market is expected to showcase significant growth during the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. The market is segmented based on grade into carbon, alloy, high-speed, and others. Among these, the alloy segment is anticipated to witness substantial growth due to its widespread use in various industries for its enhanced properties such as resistance to wear, toughness, and hardness. In terms of form, the market is divided into round bar, sheet, plate, and flat bar, with the round bar segment projected to dominate the market owing to its extensive applications in the manufacturing sector. When considering the type segmentation, water-hardening tool steel is likely to experience high demand due to its suitability for various tooling applications in diverse end-use industries. Furthermore, by application, the automotive sector is set to lead the market as tool steel finds extensive usage in the production of automotive components, driving market growth.

